TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {18281=Friday, October 24, 2008 (07:30 PM) Playoff game at Hartwood Park, LeRoy NY Section V Class C Quarterfinal LeRoy Oatkan Knights 69, South Seneca/Romulus Falcons 13, 9182=LeRoy, 8-0 on the year and ranked 3rd in the state among Class C schools, play the 4th-seeded Letchworth Indians in the first of 2 semifinal clashes to be played this Saturday, November 1st at 1 PM at Aquinas Institute. The second half of the semi doubleheader pits 2nd-seeded Oakfield-Alabama (8-0) against familiar Genesee Region rival and 3rd-seeded Pembroke (7-1) at 4 PM. All of the teams left in Class C are talented and tough - the title is definitely up for grabs., 7153=The Knights struck quickly after forcing a Falcon punt as Alexander raced 44 yards on the first play from scrimmage for a 7-0 Knights lead just 1:13 into the contest.
